title: Manufacturing Boosts US Economy As Durable Goods Orders Rise Again
text: In a splash of good news for the coronavirus-battered economy, new orders for durable goods rose 1.3 percent in October, new federal stats show. title: US corporate profits jumped a record $495 billion in the 3rd quarter as the economy reopened
text: US corporate earnings climbed at the fastest pace on record in the third quarter as economic reopening and rebounding demand lifted spending. Profits jumped $495.3 billion, or at a 27.1% annualized rate, over the three-month period, according to Commerce Department data published Wednesday. Domestic profits of financial corporations leaped $24.5 billion.
